19
00:00:31.698 --> 00:00:33.325
- Anne Marie?
- Shh.

20
00:00:35.410 --> 00:00:36.912
Did you find it?

21
00:00:38.622 --> 00:00:41.216
- I had to bribe the janitor.
- Thanks.

22
00:00:41.416 --> 00:00:43.293
I can handle labor
but not sugar withdrawal.

23
00:00:47.089 --> 00:00:48.341
Sleep tight.

24
00:00:48.549 --> 00:00:50.222
Thank you.

25
00:00:52.302 --> 00:00:54.179
Diego.

26
00:00:56.390 --> 00:00:58.267
You're perfect.

27
00:01:03.355 --> 00:01:06.734
I forgot to ask her
for a glass of water.

28
00:01:06.942 --> 00:01:08.660
I'll get you one.

29
00:01:36.221 --> 00:01:40.146
Oh. my goodness. Sister Luisa!
I'm so sorry.

30
00:01:40.350 --> 00:01:42.398
I was on my rounds
and I keep hearing this..

31
00:01:42.603 --> 00:01:44.230
The mice?

32
00:01:44.438 --> 00:01:45.530
It's this old convent.

33
00:01:45.731 --> 00:01:48.200
I still get scared
walking alone at night.

34
00:01:49.901 --> 00:01:51.778
Good night. Sister Anne Marie.

35
00:01:51.987 --> 00:01:53.455
Good night.

36
00:02:09.087 --> 00:02:11.931
Hugo?

37
00:02:17.971 --> 00:02:19.973
Martina!

38
00:02:20.140 --> 00:02:23.019
No. No. No! No!
No! Martina! Martina!

39
00:02:26.021 --> 00:02:29.025
Martina! Martina..

40
00:02:29.232 --> 00:02:31.326
No!

41
00:02:57.469 --> 00:02:59.346
Tea.

42
00:03:05.310 --> 00:03:06.857
Hmm.

43
00:03:07.062 --> 00:03:08.985
Bit traditional for my taste.

44
00:03:09.189 --> 00:03:11.362
But glad to see
your strength's coming back.

45
00:03:15.904 --> 00:03:17.872
- Oi.
- Hey!

46
00:03:18.073 --> 00:03:19.791
Does it feel good?

47
00:03:19.991 --> 00:03:20.992
Being back at it?

48
00:03:21.201 --> 00:03:23.124
Yes and no.

49
00:03:23.328 --> 00:03:25.080
I've been having nightmares
about this stuff.

50
00:03:25.288 --> 00:03:27.711
It's all I've been able to see
since we got back from Kentucky.

51
00:03:27.916 --> 00:03:29.543
Well. there's no mystery there.

52
00:03:29.751 --> 00:03:31.219
You touch an angel's heart.
you get a blast

53
00:03:31.420 --> 00:03:32.717
from the Old Testament.

54
00:03:32.921 --> 00:03:35.219
You're seeing things
that winged menace used to see.

55
00:03:35.424 --> 00:03:37.643
I thought so. too.
Until I drew this.

56
00:03:37.843 --> 00:03:39.095
Hm.

57
00:03:44.015 --> 00:03:46.859
This twisty little
horror show's an lnvunche.

58
00:03:47.060 --> 00:03:50.439
And it's right up
that angel's alley.

59
00:03:50.647 --> 00:03:52.775
Must've missed that story
in Sunday school.

60
00:03:52.983 --> 00:03:55.031
Invunche don't get
a shout out in the Good Book

61
00:03:55.235 --> 00:03:57.408
but they ripped a few throats
back in Noah's day.

62
00:03:57.612 --> 00:04:00.161
Believe me. Nasty bastards.

63
00:04:00.365 --> 00:04:01.787
Unstoppable.

64
00:04:01.992 --> 00:04:04.165
Luckily they all went out
with the last flood.

65
00:04:04.369 --> 00:04:06.212
Give the history lesson
a break. eh?

66
00:04:06.413 --> 00:04:08.882
Do the bloody crossword
or something.

67
00:04:20.635 --> 00:04:23.388
I'm sorry. I didn't know
John had a visitor.

68
00:04:23.597 --> 00:04:26.066
Where is he? I need him.

69
00:04:26.266 --> 00:04:28.360
John. did you forget someone?

70
00:04:28.560 --> 00:04:30.358
- My name is Zed by the way.
- I need him now.

71
00:04:30.562 --> 00:04:32.064
Well. clearly.

72
00:04:32.272 --> 00:04:34.274
John! John Constantine!

73
00:04:34.483 --> 00:04:36.577
Oh. geez. Good God. woman!

74
00:04:36.777 --> 00:04:38.370
I'm not deaf. alright?
I can hear you.

75
00:04:38.570 --> 00:04:40.413
Keep your bloody knickers on.

76
00:04:42.073 --> 00:04:44.667
Anne Marie?

77
00:04:44.868 --> 00:04:46.120
Are you alright?

78
00:04:48.121 --> 00:04:49.839
Would I come to you
if I was alright?

79
00:04:51.666 --> 00:04:54.215
- You didn't know she was here?
- She isn't. Where are you?

80
00:04:54.419 --> 00:04:56.842
Mexico. I need your help.

81
00:04:57.047 --> 00:04:58.799
- Are you hurt?
- No.

82
00:04:59.007 --> 00:05:01.635
Something stole a baby.
It killed the mother.

83
00:05:01.843 --> 00:05:03.345
It ripped into her.

84
00:05:03.553 --> 00:05:05.976
Hey.

85
00:05:06.181 --> 00:05:07.398
What just happened?

86
00:05:07.599 --> 00:05:08.725
Well. I told you she's not here.

87
00:05:08.934 --> 00:05:10.732
"Ripped" how? Teeth or claws?

88
00:05:10.936 --> 00:05:13.985
- This thing have fangs? Fur?
- I don't know.

89
00:05:14.189 --> 00:05:15.941
Then how do you know there's
not a mortal explanation?

90
00:05:21.196 --> 00:05:22.948
I wish it had been human.

91
00:05:23.156 --> 00:05:25.705
I would've gone
to someone else for help.

92
00:05:25.909 --> 00:05:27.001
Anyone else.

93
00:05:27.202 --> 00:05:28.499
And what's stopping you?

94
00:05:28.662 --> 00:05:30.960
There's plenty of occult experts
in Mexico.

95
00:05:31.164 --> 00:05:33.462
They don't owe me.

96
00:05:33.667 --> 00:05:35.010
You do.

97
00:05:35.210 --> 00:05:37.212
Avenue Nueva 366.

98
00:05:37.420 --> 00:05:38.842
Villa del Carban.

99
00:05:39.047 --> 00:05:40.549
Hurry.

100
00:05:43.885 --> 00:05:45.762
Avenue Nueva 366..

101
00:05:45.971 --> 00:05:47.564
What just happened?

102
00:05:47.764 --> 00:05:49.892
It's called bi-location.

103
00:05:50.100 --> 00:05:53.024
The power to be in
two places at the same time.

104
00:05:53.228 --> 00:05:54.821
It's the domain of
adventurous souls

105
00:05:55.021 --> 00:05:56.944
and the occasional saint which

106
00:05:57.148 --> 00:05:59.401
Anne Marie Flynn
most certainly isn't.

107
00:06:00.902 --> 00:06:02.529
She hates my guts.

108
00:06:02.737 --> 00:06:05.115
Must be pretty sodding desperate
to be coming to me for help.

109
00:06:29.472 --> 00:06:31.691
Ow! Bollocks!

110
00:06:31.892 --> 00:06:33.189
You should use a spoon.

111
00:06:34.853 --> 00:06:36.400
Making a purification bowl.

112
00:06:36.605 --> 00:06:38.858
Left my last good one
in Puerto Rico.

113
00:06:39.065 --> 00:06:41.033
Does the work of a priest.

114
00:06:41.234 --> 00:06:43.111
Turns water holy.

115
00:06:43.320 --> 00:06:45.414
Well. you know. I could probably

116
00:06:45.614 --> 00:06:47.708
put it in my carry-on
if you need some space.

117
00:06:47.908 --> 00:06:50.411
Well. that would be lovely
if you were going with.

118
00:06:50.619 --> 00:06:52.087
But you're still on R and R.

119
00:06:54.205 --> 00:06:55.548
You're that concerned about me?

120
00:06:55.749 --> 00:06:57.717
That's why I'm letting you
crash here.

121
00:06:57.918 --> 00:06:59.511
I'll turn the traps on
on my way out.

122
00:06:59.711 --> 00:07:02.339
The house will keep you safe
as long as you don't leave it.

123
00:07:02.547 --> 00:07:06.597
Okay. ljust have.
you know. one more question.

124
00:07:09.971 --> 00:07:11.894
I..

125
00:07:12.098 --> 00:07:14.317
You're seriously not taking
the Spanish speaker?

126
00:07:14.517 --> 00:07:17.896
I'm seriously not going there
for a conversation.

127
00:07:18.104 --> 00:07:19.321
Ah-ha!

128
00:07:19.522 --> 00:07:21.365
So. she is an old flame.

129
00:07:23.568 --> 00:07:27.948
We slept together. once.
if that's what you're after.

130
00:07:28.156 --> 00:07:30.500
Never should have though.
Wasn't the point of us.

131
00:07:34.079 --> 00:07:36.798
Magic was my salvation
growing up and..

132
00:07:36.998 --> 00:07:39.717
She hooked me up
in the occult scene.

133
00:07:39.918 --> 00:07:41.465
Is that why you "owe" her?

134
00:07:42.921 --> 00:07:44.969
No.

135
00:07:45.173 --> 00:07:46.641
She was with me at Newcastle.

136
00:07:48.927 --> 00:07:50.929
She saw what happened.

137
00:07:51.137 --> 00:07:53.686
Just like Gary.

138
00:07:53.890 --> 00:07:56.564
Swore she'd kill me
if she ever saw me again.

139
00:07:56.768 --> 00:07:59.897
I'd rather play this one out
in private. if you don't mind.

140
00:08:02.524 --> 00:08:04.117
Sounds like Chas.

141
00:08:04.317 --> 00:08:05.534
So much for privacy. huh?

142
00:08:05.735 --> 00:08:07.578
Ah. don't take it
personally. luv.

143
00:08:07.779 --> 00:08:09.497
Chas and I. we go way back.

144
00:08:09.698 --> 00:08:11.291
Remember. stay inside.

145
00:08:11.491 --> 00:08:13.789
And. uh. don't go wandering.

146
00:08:33.221 --> 00:08:35.064
Did you know we were coming
to a convent?

147
00:08:35.265 --> 00:08:36.938
It's one gory detail
she left out.

148
00:08:49.738 --> 00:08:52.457
- You should have brought Zed.
- Don't you bloody start on me.

149
00:08:52.657 --> 00:08:54.910
Uh. excuse me. luv. you don't
happen to know a British girl

150
00:08:55.118 --> 00:08:56.791
by the name
of Anne Marie Flynn. do you?

151
00:08:56.995 --> 00:08:59.043
Fairly pretty. brunette.
She kind of got this..

152
00:09:01.833 --> 00:09:03.380
Annie?

153
00:09:06.337 --> 00:09:08.510
Uh. it's great to see you.

154
00:09:08.715 --> 00:09:10.092
John didn't need to
drag you into this.

155
00:09:10.300 --> 00:09:12.553
I should've told him
to come alone.

156
00:09:12.761 --> 00:09:15.480
That's another thing you
should've told me..

157
00:09:15.680 --> 00:09:17.808
Sister.

158
00:09:18.016 --> 00:09:19.814
We can't talk here.

159
00:09:27.317 --> 00:09:29.740
The police outside work for
the man whose wife was murdered.

160
00:09:29.944 --> 00:09:31.617
They questioned everyone
who was here last night.

161
00:09:31.821 --> 00:09:34.040
No one saw anything.

162
00:09:34.240 --> 00:09:36.083
By the look of the burn
on your chest

163
00:09:36.284 --> 00:09:39.504
we're not looking for
a... human suspect.

164
00:09:39.704 --> 00:09:42.207
It's gonna take more than an
interrogation to find out what.

165
00:09:42.415 --> 00:09:43.837
The police will be leaving
for the funeral soon.

166
00:09:44.042 --> 00:09:45.794
You'll have an hour
to look around.

167
00:09:46.002 --> 00:09:47.800
Oh. come on. luv.

168
00:09:48.004 --> 00:09:49.847
You're skipping
all the juicy parts.

169
00:09:51.549 --> 00:09:54.018
No. I told you
exactly what I saw.

170
00:09:54.219 --> 00:09:55.892
You can't just sit there
in a bloody nun's habit

171
00:09:56.096 --> 00:09:58.519
and pretend we don't have
nothing to cover.

172
00:09:58.723 --> 00:10:01.192
I always figured that one
of us would flee to Mexico

173
00:10:01.392 --> 00:10:04.737
but I thought
there'd be tequila involved.

174
00:10:04.938 --> 00:10:06.406
Or skinny-dipping.

175
00:10:07.816 --> 00:10:09.534
More jokes.

176
00:10:09.734 --> 00:10:11.156
That's incredible.

177
00:10:11.361 --> 00:10:13.705
What happened to Astra
didn't change you at all.

178
00:10:16.699 --> 00:10:19.543
- Easy. Annie.
- Don't call me that.

179
00:10:19.744 --> 00:10:21.872
I don't know how you do it
but my soul can't take

180
00:10:22.080 --> 00:10:24.174
another lost child.

181
00:10:24.374 --> 00:10:26.593
I took a vow of service
to repent for my sins

182
00:10:26.793 --> 00:10:28.340
during that seance.

183
00:10:28.545 --> 00:10:29.922
What about you?

184
00:10:31.464 --> 00:10:33.057
Just because I'm not hiding
in a nunnery

185
00:10:33.258 --> 00:10:35.431
don't mean I ignore my debts.

186
00:10:37.220 --> 00:10:39.723
Sometimes I even fly to
Mexico on a moment's notice

187
00:10:39.931 --> 00:10:41.478
to very little thanks.

188
00:10:41.683 --> 00:10:44.607
Thanks?
Oh. is that why you're here?

189
00:10:44.811 --> 00:10:46.438
I'm fresh out
but you should try the others.

190
00:10:46.646 --> 00:10:49.866
Ritchie. Gary. Judith..

191
00:10:50.066 --> 00:10:55.323
Have they called you
with their gratitude?

192
00:10:55.530 --> 00:10:58.579
There's no point reeling
in the years. now. is there?

193
00:10:58.783 --> 00:11:00.877
We need to figure out
what kind of demonic killer

194
00:11:01.077 --> 00:11:03.705
walks into the house of God
without breaking a sweat.

195
00:11:47.874 --> 00:11:50.047
Is this the only place
it attacked?

196
00:11:50.251 --> 00:11:51.173
Yes.

197
00:12:06.184 --> 00:12:09.984
- That's from the mice.
- Not necessarily.

198
00:12:10.188 --> 00:12:12.657
A lot of wall-dwellers
target children.

199
00:12:12.857 --> 00:12:15.531
Duendes. fairies..

200
00:12:15.735 --> 00:12:17.408
Nursery demons.

201
00:12:17.612 --> 00:12:19.364
Grab the table. Chas.

202
00:12:19.572 --> 00:12:22.621
Our first job is to narrow
down the category.

203
00:12:22.825 --> 00:12:26.329
Rune stones will tell us which
team our culprit plays for.

204
00:12:55.483 --> 00:12:57.235
Oh! Uh... hello.

205
00:12:57.443 --> 00:12:59.241
- Can I help you?
- It's alright. Sister.

206
00:12:59.445 --> 00:13:01.743
- They're just here to..
- Crime scene cleanup.

207
00:13:01.948 --> 00:13:03.950
Yes. There's a new mother
coming in soon.

208
00:13:04.117 --> 00:13:06.461
Of course. Sorry to interrupt.

209
00:13:06.661 --> 00:13:09.289
One of the sisters saw you.

210
00:13:09.497 --> 00:13:11.795
She thought you were El Cuycuy.

211
00:13:12.000 --> 00:13:14.253
The bogeyman. Huh.

212
00:13:14.460 --> 00:13:17.964
And you just charged up here
with nothing but your wits.

213
00:13:18.172 --> 00:13:20.015
Woman after my own heart.

214
00:13:22.593 --> 00:13:24.140
Good luck.

215
00:13:24.345 --> 00:13:25.767
You. too.

216
00:13:28.224 --> 00:13:30.898
You can't even turn it off
around a woman married to God?

217
00:13:31.102 --> 00:13:34.572
What. you mean sister
flirtatious? She started it.

218
00:13:34.772 --> 00:13:37.116
If those cops are gonna be back
in an hour. we gotta move fast.

219
00:13:53.499 --> 00:13:55.217
Holy mother of earth

220
00:13:55.418 --> 00:13:57.637
mother of the higher realm

221
00:13:57.837 --> 00:14:00.090
guide my hand.

222
00:14:00.298 --> 00:14:02.392
Reveal the evil that dwelt here.

223
00:14:09.182 --> 00:14:10.855
What have we here?

224
00:14:17.732 --> 00:14:19.405
Whatever was here
covered its tracks.

225
00:14:19.609 --> 00:14:22.203
Baby snackers aren't that
sophisticated. This is good.

226
00:14:22.403 --> 00:14:24.030
It means the kid
might still be alive.

227
00:14:24.197 --> 00:14:27.201
We need a link
to the child's soul.

228
00:14:27.408 --> 00:14:29.502
The placenta. It's buried
in their backyard.

229
00:14:29.702 --> 00:14:31.921
Local tradition. It's supposed
to bring good luck.

230
00:14:32.121 --> 00:14:33.589
Fat lot of good that did.

231
00:14:33.790 --> 00:14:34.837
Alright. you stay here.

232
00:14:35.041 --> 00:14:36.463
Watch for trouble.

233
00:14:36.667 --> 00:14:37.759
We've got some digging to do.

234
00:14:39.170 --> 00:14:40.467
If the placenta's
really buried

235
00:14:40.671 --> 00:14:42.469
in Hugo's back yard
I can find it myself.

236
00:14:42.673 --> 00:14:45.142
One spell will tell me
if the tyke's alive.

237
00:14:45.343 --> 00:14:48.222
You can wait in the
van. if you're afraid.

238
00:14:48.429 --> 00:14:49.305
Who said that I was afraid?

239
00:14:49.514 --> 00:14:50.686
Well. I figured it was that or

240
00:14:50.890 --> 00:14:51.982
you just took a spontaneous

241
00:14:52.183 --> 00:14:53.810
vow of silence on the ride over.

242
00:14:54.018 --> 00:14:55.565
It couldn't possibly be
that I'm focused

243
00:14:55.770 --> 00:14:57.522
on finding a missing baby?

244
00:14:57.730 --> 00:14:59.107
Or that I don't have
anything to say to you?

245
00:14:59.315 --> 00:15:02.068
Annie. listen..

246
00:15:02.276 --> 00:15:04.370
L know you don't trust me
after the seance at Newcastle.

247
00:15:04.570 --> 00:15:05.822
Trust?

248
00:15:06.030 --> 00:15:07.873
You lost that before the seance.

249
00:15:10.159 --> 00:15:13.163
When you left my bed and went
trawling for girls at the bar?

250
00:15:13.371 --> 00:15:15.419
My sheets
weren't even cold. John.

251
00:15:15.623 --> 00:15:17.296
Yeah. I saw you.

252
00:15:19.419 --> 00:15:21.296
Do you want that vow of silence
back now?

253
00:15:48.948 --> 00:15:51.121
I didn't mean for you
to see me that night.

254
00:15:53.411 --> 00:15:55.539
I'm sorry I hurt you.

255
00:15:55.746 --> 00:15:57.919
It's not just the sex
or the seance. John.

256
00:15:58.124 --> 00:16:00.126
It's... it's your ego.

257
00:16:00.334 --> 00:16:02.177
Everyone's just a port
in your storm.

258
00:16:17.226 --> 00:16:19.320
The placenta's
definitely buried here.

259
00:16:22.857 --> 00:16:24.200
Is that skin?

260
00:16:32.575 --> 00:16:34.293
Oh!

261
00:16:39.540 --> 00:16:41.042
Oh. my God!

262
00:16:43.336 --> 00:16:44.804
Manos arriba! Hands
where I can see them!

263
00:16:45.004 --> 00:16:46.472
Hugo. wait! It's me!

264
00:16:46.672 --> 00:16:47.548
Sister?

265
00:16:47.757 --> 00:16:49.759
What are you doing?

266
00:16:49.967 --> 00:16:51.014
What is that?

267
00:16:51.219 --> 00:16:53.187
A piece of human fruit. mate.

268
00:16:53.387 --> 00:16:55.685
Your baby's alive.

269
00:16:55.890 --> 00:16:57.563
And I know who took him.

270
00:17:02.647 --> 00:17:04.695
Have another.

271
00:17:04.899 --> 00:17:07.527
It won't make more sense

272
00:17:07.693 --> 00:17:09.445
but it will make you
more open to it.

273
00:17:11.572 --> 00:17:15.998
I'll be "open" to my trees
growing human flesh?

274
00:17:16.202 --> 00:17:18.375
The placenta is
connected to an infant's soul.

275
00:17:18.579 --> 00:17:21.002
"Your son's is telling us
that there's some"

276
00:17:21.207 --> 00:17:23.335
very dark magic surrounding him.

277
00:17:23.543 --> 00:17:25.136
As old as the Garden of Eden.

278
00:17:25.336 --> 00:17:27.589
Forbidden fruit.
that ring a bell?

279
00:17:27.797 --> 00:17:30.266
If you try and tell me that
Adam or Eve took my boy..

280
00:17:31.968 --> 00:17:33.811
Not Eve.

281
00:17:34.011 --> 00:17:35.558
One of her sisters.

282
00:17:35.763 --> 00:17:39.063
They turned down Adam's
proposal before Eve said yes.

283
00:17:39.267 --> 00:17:41.770
Chose an eternity
as goddesses of hell

284
00:17:41.978 --> 00:17:43.821
over a lifetime of obedience
on Earth.

285
00:17:45.106 --> 00:17:46.983
It's hard to blame 'em. really.

286
00:17:48.609 --> 00:17:51.112
Martina was a good Catholic.

287
00:17:51.320 --> 00:17:54.039
Why would God let this
happen to her. to Diego?

288
00:17:54.240 --> 00:17:57.164
This isn't God's work. Hugo.

289
00:17:57.368 --> 00:18:01.043
Evil wins when we let it destroy
our faith in the power of good.

290
00:18:02.456 --> 00:18:04.333
Believe me.
I know how hard it is.

291
00:18:06.586 --> 00:18:09.180
I've been on the force
for 14 years.

292
00:18:09.380 --> 00:18:10.848
Never felt so helpless.

293
00:18:12.717 --> 00:18:14.435
I always thought
God was listening.

294
00:18:15.928 --> 00:18:18.647
Ah. let the Almighty
take His time out.

295
00:18:18.848 --> 00:18:20.850
We got plenty to occupy
ourselves with

296
00:18:21.058 --> 00:18:23.436
like figuring out
which one of Eve's sisters

297
00:18:23.644 --> 00:18:24.770
is behind all this.

298
00:18:28.232 --> 00:18:30.360
Now you're standing in for God.

299
00:18:30.568 --> 00:18:32.991
Make way for John Constantine.

300
00:18:33.195 --> 00:18:35.414
I'm telling a desperate man
that there are things we can do

301
00:18:35.615 --> 00:18:37.834
to get his son back
other than pray.

302
00:18:38.034 --> 00:18:39.877
Your arrogance
is out of control.

303
00:18:44.081 --> 00:18:45.628
It took another baby.

304
00:18:54.216 --> 00:18:56.469
- Considering a blue period?
- Hey!

305
00:18:56.677 --> 00:18:58.099
- Hi.
- Eddie.

306
00:18:58.304 --> 00:19:00.523
Uh. sorry.
I didn't recognize you with

307
00:19:00.723 --> 00:19:02.316
um. your clothes on.

308
00:19:03.768 --> 00:19:05.315
What are you doing here?

309
00:19:05.519 --> 00:19:08.193
Well. I'm only modeling
until my art career takes off.

310
00:19:09.774 --> 00:19:11.492
You paint. too?

311
00:19:11.692 --> 00:19:13.990
I'll tell you about it
over drinks.

312
00:19:14.195 --> 00:19:16.038
First round's on me?

313
00:19:16.238 --> 00:19:17.535
Let me pay for these. first.

314
00:19:30.211 --> 00:19:32.680
Um. I finished my MBA
three years ago.

315
00:19:32.838 --> 00:19:35.057
I don't know.
I can't bring myself to..

316
00:19:35.257 --> 00:19:37.476
Put on a tie and go to work.

317
00:19:37.677 --> 00:19:39.520
So you strip naked
and pose nude.

318
00:19:39.720 --> 00:19:40.937
Oh. yeah. it's a cry for help.

319
00:19:43.474 --> 00:19:46.273
So what about you?
How long you been studying art?

320
00:19:46.477 --> 00:19:48.730
- It's my first class.
- No. I don't believe that.

321
00:19:48.938 --> 00:19:50.690
I-I saw your sketches.

322
00:19:52.400 --> 00:19:54.494
Drawing..

323
00:19:54.694 --> 00:19:55.991
It's like breathing to me.

324
00:19:56.195 --> 00:19:57.822
Hmm.

325
00:19:58.030 --> 00:19:59.498
I'd love to see your work.

326
00:20:00.700 --> 00:20:02.953
No. you wouldn't.

327
00:20:03.160 --> 00:20:04.377
You really wouldn't.

328
00:20:11.293 --> 00:20:12.670
That beer go to your head?

329
00:20:16.549 --> 00:20:19.393
No. No. I..

330
00:20:19.552 --> 00:20:21.350
Promise I'm not that much
of a lightweight.

331
00:20:21.554 --> 00:20:23.227
Ah. okay.
That sounds like a challenge.

332
00:20:23.431 --> 00:20:25.479
Hey. why don't we do
the next round at my place?

333
00:20:27.977 --> 00:20:29.103
Okay.

334
00:20:31.522 --> 00:20:33.024
Why didn't I wake up?

335
00:20:33.232 --> 00:20:34.700
It's good that you didn't.

336
00:20:34.900 --> 00:20:36.026
It may have saved your life.

337
00:20:36.235 --> 00:20:37.327
We're going to find her.

338
00:20:37.528 --> 00:20:38.871
We'll start by dusting
for prints.

339
00:20:39.071 --> 00:20:42.041
There won't be any prints.

340
00:21:00.384 --> 00:21:02.603
Oi! So. uh..

341
00:21:02.803 --> 00:21:04.601
If I'm reading this right

342
00:21:04.805 --> 00:21:07.103
this teenager's your son

343
00:21:07.308 --> 00:21:10.027
and the new missing baby is..

344
00:21:10.227 --> 00:21:11.945
Your granddaughter.

345
00:21:12.146 --> 00:21:14.069
Did you piss off a Gypsy. mate?

346
00:21:14.273 --> 00:21:16.116
Get your whole brood cursed?

347
00:21:17.526 --> 00:21:19.574
The killer is targeting
your family.

348
00:21:19.779 --> 00:21:22.123
You two just. uh.
carry on catching up.

349
00:21:22.323 --> 00:21:24.417
I got a guilty goddess to catch.

350
00:21:24.617 --> 00:21:26.210
Does that fountain outside work?

351
00:21:34.960 --> 00:21:36.212
I can't let you summon some

352
00:21:36.420 --> 00:21:38.093
deity from hell
on the convent grounds.

353
00:21:38.297 --> 00:21:39.674
I'm only casting a spell
to invoke

354
00:21:39.882 --> 00:21:41.099
the goddess' reflection
in the water.

355
00:21:41.300 --> 00:21:43.018
That way. I can put a name
to the face.

356
00:21:43.219 --> 00:21:45.347
And what happens when your spell
gets out of control. John?

357
00:21:45.554 --> 00:21:46.771
This convent's full
of innocent people.

358
00:21:46.972 --> 00:21:48.599
Then why did you call me?

359
00:21:48.808 --> 00:21:50.310
Saving lives requires choices

360
00:21:50.518 --> 00:21:53.442
that you're not willing to make
or I wouldn't be here.

361
00:21:53.646 --> 00:21:55.364
Now go and pray and let me work.

362
00:22:01.153 --> 00:22:03.030
Was that really necessary?

363
00:22:14.041 --> 00:22:17.011
I've heard worse from him.

364
00:22:17.211 --> 00:22:20.761
He'd rather risk your feelings
than any other part of you.

365
00:22:20.965 --> 00:22:22.342
That's how..

366
00:22:22.550 --> 00:22:24.393
he deals with the pain.

367
00:22:26.220 --> 00:22:28.518
John has one thing
that makes his life

368
00:22:28.722 --> 00:22:31.191
worth a damn and he can't do it
if he lets anyone in too close.

369
00:22:33.185 --> 00:22:34.607
Like he did with you.

370
00:22:44.488 --> 00:22:45.740
That's all.

371
00:22:48.826 --> 00:22:50.669
Alright. sisters of Eve..

372
00:22:52.246 --> 00:22:55.716
Whichever one of you
is hanging around..

373
00:22:55.916 --> 00:22:58.294
It's time to reveal
your pretty mug.

374
00:23:11.599 --> 00:23:13.397
Axis mundi produco

375
00:23:13.601 --> 00:23:15.603
tuus vires.

376
00:23:15.811 --> 00:23:17.108
Axis mundi produco

377
00:23:17.313 --> 00:23:18.439
tuus vires.

378
00:23:22.651 --> 00:23:25.279
Hola. sister. I'm. uh..

379
00:23:25.487 --> 00:23:27.660
Involved in
a personal prayer here

380
00:23:27.865 --> 00:23:29.708
if you don't mind
clearing out a sec.

381
00:23:29.909 --> 00:23:32.628
Uh. we need you upstairs.
Yolanda is very upset.

382
00:23:32.828 --> 00:23:34.250
You left everyone in confusion.

383
00:23:34.455 --> 00:23:36.048
Oh. you just tell them
to relax. alright?

384
00:23:36.248 --> 00:23:38.751
We'll get everything sorted.

385
00:23:38.959 --> 00:23:41.883
If you don't come with me now.
you'll be the one sorted out

386
00:23:42.087 --> 00:23:44.681
by Mother Superior
or the police.

387
00:23:48.719 --> 00:23:50.517
It's funny. your timing here.

388
00:23:50.721 --> 00:23:52.268
You know.
if I didn't know better

389
00:23:52.473 --> 00:23:54.817
I'd say you're trying to keep me
away from this here fountain.

390
00:23:56.518 --> 00:23:58.520
Let's go. Now.

391
00:23:59.855 --> 00:24:01.732
Okay.

392
00:24:01.941 --> 00:24:03.284
I'll just rinse out my bowl.

393
00:24:13.911 --> 00:24:16.630
Forgive me. sister.

394
00:24:16.830 --> 00:24:19.083
Your name slipped my mind.

395
00:24:21.001 --> 00:24:22.298
Lilith. is it?

396
00:24:22.503 --> 00:24:23.629
Durgia.

397
00:24:23.837 --> 00:24:26.340
Naamah.

398
00:24:26.548 --> 00:24:27.925
Lamashtu.

399
00:24:33.430 --> 00:24:36.775
Where are the babies?

400
00:25:10.384 --> 00:25:12.887
Wow. You live here by yourself?

401
00:25:13.095 --> 00:25:15.097
I'm house-sitting.

402
00:25:15.305 --> 00:25:18.184
Well. you have
very interesting friends.

403
00:25:18.392 --> 00:25:21.566
Yes. I do have very
interesting friends.

404
00:25:21.770 --> 00:25:23.647
Whoa!

405
00:25:23.856 --> 00:25:25.324
- It's nice. right?
- Yeah.

406
00:25:25.524 --> 00:25:26.741
Yeah.

407
00:25:36.493 --> 00:25:39.167
I can't wait for you to meet
them when they get home.

408
00:25:39.371 --> 00:25:42.215
They love interrogations.
Why are you following me?

409
00:25:44.168 --> 00:25:46.341
Your father wants you home.

410
00:25:48.797 --> 00:25:50.891
What did you say?

411
00:25:51.091 --> 00:25:54.015
We just wanna talk to you. Mary.

412
00:25:54.219 --> 00:25:57.063
Don't you ever. ever call me
that again!

413
00:26:00.267 --> 00:26:02.235
Her name isn't Louisa.

414
00:26:02.436 --> 00:26:04.234
It's Lamashtu.

415
00:26:04.438 --> 00:26:07.282
Eve's youngest sister and
a bit of a glorified vampire.

416
00:26:07.483 --> 00:26:10.737
I taught you about Lamashtu.
She doesn't kidnap her prey.

417
00:26:12.446 --> 00:26:14.039
What does she do?

418
00:26:14.239 --> 00:26:18.289
Lamashtu enjoys babies
for their nutritional value.

419
00:26:18.494 --> 00:26:21.043
But lucky for you.
she's curbing her hunger

420
00:26:21.246 --> 00:26:24.625
though I can't conceive why.
Lamashtu lives to feed.

421
00:26:24.833 --> 00:26:26.460
Maybe the question is
what makes Hugo's litter

422
00:26:26.668 --> 00:26:28.170
worth keeping alive?

423
00:26:28.378 --> 00:26:30.051
We're nobodies.
we're good Catholics.

424
00:26:30.255 --> 00:26:31.632
I've got nothing to hide
from you.

425
00:26:31.840 --> 00:26:34.093
Maybe someone's hiding
something from you.

426
00:26:34.301 --> 00:26:36.053
And what about the rest
of your family?

427
00:26:36.261 --> 00:26:38.434
- Who knows your roots?
- How about my grandmother. Pia?

428
00:26:38.639 --> 00:26:39.891
She was born in Chile.

429
00:26:40.099 --> 00:26:43.649
Great. I have a way
with older women.

430
00:26:48.107 --> 00:26:50.860
Thank you. abuelita.

431
00:26:51.068 --> 00:26:52.570
- Is that Mateo?
- No. no.

432
00:26:52.778 --> 00:26:54.496
I'm just a friend of Hugo's.

433
00:26:54.696 --> 00:26:56.664
I have some questions
about Chile.

434
00:26:56.865 --> 00:26:58.287
He said that you're the expert.

435
00:26:58.492 --> 00:27:01.120
- Chile?
- Pia. listen to me.

436
00:27:01.328 --> 00:27:03.547
Something is coming
after our babies.

437
00:27:03.747 --> 00:27:05.340
Something inhuman.

438
00:27:05.541 --> 00:27:07.214
Martina is dead. abuelita.

439
00:27:09.128 --> 00:27:11.381
Why would someone be
targeting us?

440
00:27:11.588 --> 00:27:13.135
God help us.

441
00:27:14.842 --> 00:27:17.436
They are back.

442
00:27:17.636 --> 00:27:19.684
Who is. Mrs. Lopez?

443
00:27:19.888 --> 00:27:22.767
La Brujeria.

444
00:27:22.975 --> 00:27:25.979
La Brujeria.

445
00:27:26.186 --> 00:27:28.188
They are tracking us down.

446
00:27:28.397 --> 00:27:30.070
Gathering new blood.

447
00:27:30.274 --> 00:27:32.447
I've never heard of La Brujeria.

448
00:27:32.651 --> 00:27:35.780
They were powerful warlocks in
Chile long before it was Chile.

449
00:27:35.988 --> 00:27:38.116
It's prehistoric stuff
they've been gone for eons.

450
00:27:38.323 --> 00:27:41.327
No. not gone.

451
00:27:41.535 --> 00:27:44.129
In hiding.

452
00:27:44.329 --> 00:27:45.797
How come I've never heard
of them?

453
00:27:45.998 --> 00:27:48.421
Because they don't exist
anymore.

454
00:27:48.625 --> 00:27:50.719
When I was a girl..

455
00:27:50.919 --> 00:27:54.014
My grandfather
was one of those..

456
00:27:54.214 --> 00:27:56.262
Monsters.

457
00:27:56.466 --> 00:27:59.185
They live to cause pain.

458
00:27:59.386 --> 00:28:02.981
My father ran away
for all of us.

459
00:28:10.981 --> 00:28:12.733
Don't add up.

460
00:28:12.941 --> 00:28:14.739
Brujeria wielded a magic
the world hasn't seen

461
00:28:14.943 --> 00:28:16.820
since God turned on the lights.

462
00:28:17.029 --> 00:28:19.407
He struck them down. Not even
hell would give them asylum.

463
00:28:19.615 --> 00:28:21.162
- They were annihilated.
- You don't believe her?

464
00:28:21.366 --> 00:28:24.336
I can't believe them. I don't
have a spell to shut down

465
00:28:24.536 --> 00:28:26.789
the brujeria. Anne Marie.
Nobody does.

466
00:28:26.997 --> 00:28:28.874
- She's speaking gibberish.
- Then why are you scared?

467
00:28:29.082 --> 00:28:30.459
I'm not scared.

468
00:28:30.667 --> 00:28:32.510
If the Brujeria were back.
we'd know it. alright?

469
00:28:32.711 --> 00:28:34.554
It wouldn't be subtle.
there would be..

470
00:28:37.716 --> 00:28:39.138
Bugger me.

471
00:28:39.343 --> 00:28:40.936
What is it?

472
00:28:41.136 --> 00:28:43.730
The rising darkness. it's. uh..

473
00:28:43.931 --> 00:28:46.025
What I checked myself out
of the asylum to fight.

474
00:28:46.225 --> 00:28:49.354
If... the brujeria are behind it..

475
00:28:53.357 --> 00:28:55.030
I can see it now.
it's not that you don't care

476
00:28:55.234 --> 00:28:57.578
it's that you can't care about
anybody and do what you do.

477
00:29:02.449 --> 00:29:05.123
I think I did come here to hide.

478
00:29:05.327 --> 00:29:07.546
And it doesn't work.

479
00:29:07.746 --> 00:29:09.373
Under this disguise.
I'm the same scared girl

480
00:29:09.581 --> 00:29:11.424
I was at Newcastle.

481
00:29:15.462 --> 00:29:17.180
Disguise.

482
00:29:17.381 --> 00:29:20.305
If Lamashtu wants a baby
with Hugo's blood..

483
00:29:20.509 --> 00:29:22.261
Then I say we give her one.

484
00:29:25.264 --> 00:29:27.517
Once we fill the poultry
with Hugo's blood

485
00:29:27.724 --> 00:29:31.649
I'll use a glamour spell to
make it look like an infant.

486
00:29:31.853 --> 00:29:34.026
We'll hand it off
to our evil lady friend

487
00:29:34.231 --> 00:29:37.701
and she will kindly lead us
to her baby stash.

488
00:29:37.901 --> 00:29:39.403
If Lamashtu is working
for the brujeria

489
00:29:39.611 --> 00:29:40.863
you'd be walking
right onto their radar.

490
00:29:41.071 --> 00:29:43.540
Well. I didn't say
there weren't risks.

491
00:29:43.740 --> 00:29:45.413
How do you know
she won't attack you first?

492
00:29:45.617 --> 00:29:48.040
I'll present the baby
as a mother's offering.

493
00:29:48.245 --> 00:29:49.792
She'll have no reason
to hurt me.

494
00:29:49.997 --> 00:29:52.750
You tried to kill Lamashtu.
She won't come near you.

495
00:29:52.958 --> 00:29:54.380
No. that's a good point.

496
00:29:54.584 --> 00:29:57.258
I'll have to dress as a woman.

497
00:29:57.462 --> 00:29:59.590
Just need me a skirt and a wig.

498
00:29:59.798 --> 00:30:01.641
- Stop it.
- Stop what?

499
00:30:01.800 --> 00:30:04.144
This kind of pathetic ruse might
have worked with Gary Lester

500
00:30:04.344 --> 00:30:07.268
but I think I deserve
a little more respect.

501
00:30:07.472 --> 00:30:09.645
I have no idea what
you're talking about. luv.

502
00:30:09.850 --> 00:30:11.227
You need me
to make this offering.

503
00:30:11.435 --> 00:30:12.857
You're counting on it.

504
00:30:17.399 --> 00:30:19.777
Look. we had our shot
at life. Annie.

505
00:30:19.985 --> 00:30:22.659
We've made our mistakes.
but these. these are..

506
00:30:22.863 --> 00:30:25.457
They're babies.

507
00:30:25.657 --> 00:30:28.331
No price is too high
to save the innocent.

508
00:30:31.163 --> 00:30:32.665
Thank you for your honesty.

509
00:30:35.834 --> 00:30:37.507
I'll make the handoff.

510
00:31:02.569 --> 00:31:04.412
You don't need to fight.

511
00:31:04.613 --> 00:31:06.832
Our father wants
what's best for you.

512
00:31:07.032 --> 00:31:10.377
Oh. so he's your
father. too. now. is he?

513
00:31:10.577 --> 00:31:12.295
Funny.

514
00:31:12.496 --> 00:31:14.965
I don't remember you
from my childhood.

515
00:31:15.165 --> 00:31:17.668
Maybe it's because
I spent most of it..

516
00:31:17.876 --> 00:31:18.968
In a locked room.

517
00:31:19.169 --> 00:31:20.341
That was for your protection.

518
00:31:20.545 --> 00:31:21.671
You know what you mean to us.

519
00:31:21.880 --> 00:31:23.257
You're our salvation.

520
00:31:23.465 --> 00:31:24.967
Eddie.

521
00:31:25.175 --> 00:31:26.518
Is that even your real name?

522
00:31:28.887 --> 00:31:30.514
How did you find me?

523
00:31:30.722 --> 00:31:32.019
We're the Crusade.

524
00:31:32.224 --> 00:31:34.226
Our believers are everywhere.

525
00:31:34.434 --> 00:31:35.811
We will always find you.

526
00:31:38.814 --> 00:31:40.532
Damn it. Eddie!

527
00:31:40.732 --> 00:31:42.450
You led them up here?

528
00:31:42.651 --> 00:31:43.823
You don't know what they are!

529
00:31:53.120 --> 00:31:55.088
One more step..

530
00:31:55.247 --> 00:31:56.339
And I'll kill him.

531
00:31:59.167 --> 00:32:00.760
I'm so sorry.

532
00:32:00.961 --> 00:32:04.181
You should be. Could've made
this much easier on all of us.

533
00:32:04.381 --> 00:32:06.679
Awake or asleep?

534
00:32:06.883 --> 00:32:08.351
Your choice.

535
00:32:09.970 --> 00:32:11.563
May be a few minutes
before Lamashtu arrives

536
00:32:11.763 --> 00:32:14.858
but she'll sniff out the blood.

537
00:32:15.058 --> 00:32:17.060
Now. do you remember the words?

538
00:32:17.269 --> 00:32:18.612
Take this child
into your dark womb

539
00:32:18.812 --> 00:32:20.655
and give it eternal life.

540
00:32:23.984 --> 00:32:27.158
You know..

541
00:32:27.362 --> 00:32:30.582
You know you never had
anything to repent for..

542
00:32:30.782 --> 00:32:32.500
Newcastle.

543
00:32:32.701 --> 00:32:34.169
That was my failure.

544
00:32:35.871 --> 00:32:37.999
You don't owe nothing for that.

545
00:32:38.206 --> 00:32:39.503
You're wrong. John.

546
00:32:39.708 --> 00:32:44.384
I owe an anxious 15-year-old boy
with no self worth.

547
00:32:44.588 --> 00:32:48.434
Always hiding from your father
and aching for a mum.

548
00:32:48.633 --> 00:32:50.010
Should've shagged you then
but instead

549
00:32:50.218 --> 00:32:51.936
I introduced you to my world.

550
00:32:54.181 --> 00:32:56.525
It was a world of wonders.

551
00:32:56.725 --> 00:32:58.193
Which you followed into hell.

552
00:33:00.020 --> 00:33:01.897
You are my failure. John.

553
00:33:03.565 --> 00:33:05.408
It's a matter of perspective.

554
00:33:11.490 --> 00:33:14.619
- 'What is this?
- The icon of Pazuzu.

555
00:33:14.826 --> 00:33:17.124
It's a bastardly demon.

556
00:33:17.329 --> 00:33:20.082
Used to be Lamashtu's soul mate.

557
00:33:20.290 --> 00:33:22.634
But now she hates his guts.

558
00:33:22.834 --> 00:33:24.461
I can relate.

559
00:34:23.687 --> 00:34:26.611
Take this child
into your dark womb

560
00:34:26.815 --> 00:34:28.283
and give it eternal life.

561
00:35:18.908 --> 00:35:23.129
- She fell for it.
- Of course she did.

562
00:35:23.330 --> 00:35:24.627
Hugo. no!

563
00:35:29.919 --> 00:35:32.263
Hugo. stop! Hugo. Hugo.

564
00:35:32.464 --> 00:35:35.217
lf you wanna see your son alive.
you got to let us do what we do.

565
00:35:35.425 --> 00:35:37.052
Look. I know
your heart's in the right place

566
00:35:37.260 --> 00:35:38.853
but you'll kill him.

567
00:35:39.054 --> 00:35:41.227
Okay. go. Go.
Go. Take-take this!

568
00:35:41.431 --> 00:35:43.729
- No. I have no use for that.
- I'll take it.

569
00:36:43.326 --> 00:36:45.294
I'm guessing that our lady
friend just discovered

570
00:36:45.495 --> 00:36:47.623
that her baby
is really a bloody chicken.

571
00:36:47.831 --> 00:36:49.378
It's not a good idea
to split up.

572
00:36:49.582 --> 00:36:52.210
We have to.
We can't lose her now.

573
00:36:52.419 --> 00:36:54.763
If you need me. scream.

574
00:36:54.963 --> 00:37:01.517
That won't be a problem for me.

575
00:37:18.903 --> 00:37:20.371
Shh.

576
00:37:36.254 --> 00:37:37.722
- Shh.
- Oh.

577
00:37:37.922 --> 00:37:39.048
Oh.

578
00:37:48.099 --> 00:37:49.646
I knew that spell
wouldn't last forever.

579
00:37:49.851 --> 00:37:54.652
The Pazuzu icon. Give it to me.

580
00:37:57.817 --> 00:37:59.785
Bring me the young bruja.

581
00:37:59.986 --> 00:38:01.829
John. give me Diego.

582
00:38:05.158 --> 00:38:07.160
The way I see it
I've got something

583
00:38:07.368 --> 00:38:10.292
you're supposed to deliver
intact. Am I wrong?

584
00:38:10.497 --> 00:38:12.124
John. that's an innocent child.

585
00:38:12.290 --> 00:38:14.418
You're working
for the brujeria. Why?

586
00:38:17.003 --> 00:38:19.256
If you don't answer me.
so help me God

587
00:38:19.464 --> 00:38:22.217
I will snap the neck
of your precious little cargo.

588
00:38:22.425 --> 00:38:24.678
and then you'll have to explain
to them why you failed.

589
00:38:24.886 --> 00:38:27.139
Now. why are you working
for the brujeria?

590
00:38:27.305 --> 00:38:29.854
They're expanding my domain.

591
00:38:30.058 --> 00:38:32.481
- In hell?
- On earth.

592
00:38:32.685 --> 00:38:35.484
John. don't do this.
Don't play this game.

593
00:38:35.647 --> 00:38:36.944
- How?
- Not now.

594
00:38:37.148 --> 00:38:40.527
What's their plan?

595
00:38:40.735 --> 00:38:42.032
Or maybe I'll just drown
the kid. eh?

596
00:38:42.237 --> 00:38:44.160
John. stop this!
Give me Diego now!

597
00:38:44.364 --> 00:38:46.617
You've got three seconds
to tell me what kind of mayhem

598
00:38:46.825 --> 00:38:48.998
they're gonna unleash.
What is their plan?

599
00:38:49.202 --> 00:38:51.330
They've figured out
how to break the boundary.

600
00:38:51.538 --> 00:38:53.586
Hell and earth
will become one.

601
00:38:53.790 --> 00:38:56.634
No more hiding like cowards
in the shadows.

602
00:38:56.835 --> 00:39:00.430
We'll live in the open
and you'll be the ones hiding.

603
00:39:00.630 --> 00:39:03.133
But there'll be no hiding
from us.

604
00:39:03.341 --> 00:39:04.888
You'll be ours.

605
00:39:06.970 --> 00:39:08.847
So that's what's on the way.

606
00:39:10.807 --> 00:39:12.855
Ambitious.

607
00:39:13.059 --> 00:39:14.311
Too bad you won't see it.

608
00:39:14.519 --> 00:39:16.988
You don't have the power
to stop me.

609
00:39:17.188 --> 00:39:18.690
No man does.

610
00:39:18.898 --> 00:39:22.152
I bet your old mate Pazuzu
sees things differently.

611
00:39:22.360 --> 00:39:24.408
How 'bout I just leave
you two lovebirds to

612
00:39:24.612 --> 00:39:25.864
sort it out. eh?

613
00:39:26.072 --> 00:39:28.666
Kaskassu sutu ilu

614
00:39:28.867 --> 00:39:31.620
il Pazuzu

615
00:39:31.828 --> 00:39:33.296
Kunu.

616
00:39:37.166 --> 00:39:38.918
Bel-palluhi

617
00:39:39.127 --> 00:39:41.425
nabu kunu utukku

618
00:39:52.849 --> 00:39:55.352
- John?
- We're alive! We're on our way!

619
00:39:57.520 --> 00:40:03.653
I'll take care of them
from here.

620
00:40:27.383 --> 00:40:29.886
- Time to go home now.
- No!

621
00:40:30.094 --> 00:40:31.812
No!

622
00:40:35.767 --> 00:40:38.111
- Is everybody okay?
- Right as rain. mate.

623
00:40:38.311 --> 00:40:41.815
Go. Now.

624
00:40:47.904 --> 00:40:52.375
Is there another one?

625
00:41:03.795 --> 00:41:05.217
What is that?

626
00:41:05.421 --> 00:41:07.719
It can't be.

627
00:41:07.924 --> 00:41:10.018
An lnvunche.

628
00:41:10.218 --> 00:41:11.891
- We have to run.
- No. no. no.

629
00:41:12.095 --> 00:41:13.722
It'll just attack us.

630
00:41:13.930 --> 00:41:15.898
We can't outrun it.

631
00:41:16.099 --> 00:41:17.976
What do we do?

632
00:41:18.184 --> 00:41:19.652
I..

633
00:41:21.521 --> 00:41:22.989
I've got no idea.

634
00:41:30.863 --> 00:41:33.662
No. no. no. You shoot that gun.
it's gonna attack us for sure.

635
00:41:33.866 --> 00:41:35.664
No. John.

636
00:41:35.827 --> 00:41:39.206
It will attack you.

637
00:41:39.414 --> 00:41:41.758
No price is too high
to save the innocent.

638
00:41:44.669 --> 00:41:46.296
Oh. you're a quick study. luv.

639
00:42:04.981 --> 00:42:06.483
Chas?!

640
00:42:06.507 --> 00:42:08.507
http://hiqve.com/
